> Good news, friends: The path to sweet-and-savory dinner bliss is only 20 minutes away! In this recipe, turkey and green beans are coated in a sumptuous sweet chili sauce, then topped with fresh cilantro and crispy fried onions. Everything comes together over a bed of fluffy rice. The results? A symphony of flavors and textures so delicious, you might just lick the bowl.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water,
and a @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low
simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Trim @green beans{6%oz} if necessary; cut crosswise into 2-inch-long
pieces.

Quarter @lime{1}.

Pick @cilantro{1/4%oz} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

> TIP: Swap in tofu or beef for turkey if preferred.

Press @tofu{1%oz} to drain; press out excess water with #paper towels{}.
Halve crosswise, then stand tofu upright and halve vertically. Lay flat
and cut into 3/4-inch cubes.

> For turkey version: Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{}
over medium-high heat. Add turkey; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Using
a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on
bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}. Break up meat into pieces and continue cooking until
turkey is cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes} more.

While turkey cooks, add green beans and a splash of water to a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}; cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until tender,
~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: No microwave? No problem! Steam beans in a small pot with a splash
> of water until just tender, 5-7 minutes.

Carefully drain any excess water.

To pan with turkey (or tofu), stir in cooked green beans, @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz}, and 1 TBSP @butter{2%tbsp}.
Cook, stirring, until turkey mixture is thoroughly coated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in a squeeze of lime juice to taste.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in 1 TBSP butter. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Divide between bowls and top with turkey stir-fry. Sprinkle with
@crispy fried onions{1}(sprinkle) and chopped cilantro. Serve with any
remaining lime wedges on the side.